To install everything, you might use:
cd /usr/local/bin; ln -s /usr/src/public/fileutils-3.2/bin/* .
cd /usr/local/man/cat1; ln -s /usr/src/public/fileutils-3.2/man/cat1/* .

To recompile, cd to the fileutils-3.2 directory and type 'make'.  Gcc
should not report any errors or warnings.

To reconfigure, type 'sh configure' (or 'bash configure' if you have
bash since it works better with configure than ash does).

The install directories is set to
/usr/src/public/fileutils-3.2/{bin,man}, though there are no paths
compiled into the executables.  The preformatted manpages are in
man/cat1.  To regenerate the preformatted manual pages, cd to man and
type 'sh catman'.

The unmodified sources are available via anonymous ftp from
prep.ai.mit.edu in directory /pub/gnu and file fileutils-3.2.tar.Z.

